{"type":"message","id":"82496940","parentId":"be493164","timestamp":"2026-04-02T08:43:59.106Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_39f4880aa94c4ca081734ab6","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"WiFi 6 HE TB STBC pre-FEC padding even symbols N_SYM initialization\",\n  \"provider\": \"firecrawl\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 2902,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"firecrawl\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ed7a03dd21960bf6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPadding method for aggregated ppdu in enhancement of ieee ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ed7a03dd21960bf6\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://patents.google.com/patent/US20220053371A1/en\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e137a5a37460ec90\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n... init = 4 ( 3 ). [0122]. For an HE SU PPDU and HE ER SU PPDU, the number of pre-FEC pad bits is calculated using Eq. (4). N PAD,Pre-FEC=(N SYM,init −m STBC)N ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e137a5a37460ec90\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"patents.google.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0c1d7c65b380f7fd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[DOC] 11-19-0793\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"0c1d7c65b380f7fd\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://mentor.ieee.org/802.11/dcn/19/11-19-0793-01-00ax-remaining-phy-math-comment-resolutions.docx\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6da18d25eeb5e7ec\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nFor HE TB PPDU in response to a trigger frame, Tthe AP indicates the UL Length, Pre-FEC Padding Factor, UL STBC and LDPC Extra Symbol Segment fields in the ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"6da18d25eeb5e7ec\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"mentor.ieee.o